text: This sindon tha land gemere the Eadmund king gebocade in to sancte Eadmunde.
Thonne is thær ærest suth be eahta treowen.
And thonne up be Alhmundes treowen.
And swa forth to Osulfes lea.
And swa forth on gerihte be manige hyllan.
And swa forth <to> <fouuer> <hagas> <&> <sua> æfter than we se Lytlantune & thonen ofer tha ea æfter than wege to Bertenedene.
And swa on gerichte east to Holegate.
And swa forth an furlang be easten Bromleage & thonan suth to niwantune meaduwe.
